Archips fervidana, the oak webworm moth, is a moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found from Maine and Quebec to North Carolina, west to Wisconsin and Arkansas.

The wingspan is 18â€“25 mm. The forewings are orange and grey, with a median band of orange that includes two dark brown blotches.  Beyond this median band, there is a band of dark grey followed by several grey lines near the apex. The fringe is dirty beige.The larvae feed on Carya and Quercus species.